    {
      "text": "Money markets and bond yields follow the new path for short rates. Longer-term rates move on expectations, like a relay race where the first runner’s speed sets the team’s pace.",
      "title": "Market rates ripple outward"
    },
    {
      "text": "Higher rates usually lift the currency as foreign money chases returns; lower rates can weaken it. The exchange rate shifts import prices and export demand, like changing the store’s price tags.",
      "title": "The currency adjusts"
