{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "You feed the compiler a source file. It first strips away trivia—whitespace, comments, line breaks—so the real signal can flow forward, like rinsing ingredients before cooking.",
      "title": "Source hits the front door"
    },
    {
      "text": "The token stream runs through the parser, which snaps tokens into a grammar-shaped scaffold. If pieces don’t fit (missing ;, wrong nesting), the build halts right here with a syntax error.",
      "title": "Parser assembles the grammar"
    },
    {
      "text": "Now walk the tree and watch names get linked to meanings. Identifiers are looked up, scopes open/close like nested rooms, and each use is tied to a declaration—or flagged as “not found.”",
      "title": "Names latch onto declarations"
    },
    {
      "text": "The compiler checks types like matching plugs to sockets. Expressions are annotated, conversions may be inserted, and mismatches trigger errors before anything lower-level is produced.",
      "title": "Types get verified and patched"
    },
    {
      "text": "Next the compiler lowers high-level constructs into IR operations. Think “desugar”: a for-loop unfolds into labels and jumps; complex expressions become simpler steps that are easy to optimize.",
      "title": "AST lowers into IR actions"
    },
    {
      "text": "IR is cleaned up and reshaped: constants get folded, dead code gets swept away, and redundant work is merged. It’s like reorganizing an assembly line to remove wasted motion.",
      "title": "Optimizers rewrite the IR"
    },
    {
      "text": "Control flow is analyzed like a city map: blocks, branches, and loops are charted. Data-flow facts (what’s available where) propagate until the compiler reaches a stable “no more changes” state.",
      "title": "Flow facts ripple through graphs"
    },
    {
      "text": "IR instructions are matched to target instructions, then registers are assigned like seats in a crowded theater. If there aren’t enough, some values “spill” to memory and get loaded back later.",
      "title": "Codegen picks ops and registers"
